def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    # NOTE: This doesn't deal with hierarchical columns yet

    if isinstance(data, Series):
        index = data.index
        dummy_index = Index(range(index.nlevels), name="__placeholder__")
        dummy = data.reindex(index=dummy_index, method='ffill')

        unstacked = dummy.unstack("__placeholder__", fill_value=fill_value)

        unstacked.index = index.levels + (clocs[0],)
    else:
        index = data.index
        cols = [idx for idx, name in enumerate(index.names) if name in clocs]
        level_values = [index.get_level_values(lvl) for lvl in cols]
        unstacked = data.unstack(level_values)
        unstacked.columns = data.columns.levels[cols] + (clocs,)

    return unstacked
